HEADWORD: Underprop
<hw>Un`der*prop"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To prop from
beneath; to put a prop under; to support; to uphold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Underprop</qex> the head that bears the crown.</q>
<rj><qau>Fenton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underproportioned</ent>⟦br⟧
